tted on time - in direct contradiction to the findings in CAS' decision.\", \"from\": 531, \"to\": 740, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 539, \"end\": 542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.525721419331394e-22, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 726, \"end\": 729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.525721419331394e-22, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Chiles' fundamental 'right\", \"from\": 552, \"to\": 578}, {\"ngram\": \"the video evidence\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 634}, {\"ngram\": \"her inquiry\", \"from\": 647, \"to\": 658}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 676, \"to\": 680}, {\"ngram\": \"direct contradiction\", \"from\": 686, \"to\": 706}, {\"ngram\": \"the findings\", \"from\": 710, \"to\": 722}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Second, the entire CAS proceeding was unfair because Chiles was not properly informed that Hamid G. Gharavi, the President of the CAS panel that revoked Chiles's bronze medal and awarded it instead to a Romanian gymnast, had a serious conflict of interest: Mr. Gharavi has acted as counsel for Romania for almost a decade and was actively representing Romania at the time of the CAS arbitration.\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 1138, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 762, \"end\": 765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.525721419331394e-22, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\